            "product_text_content_1": "<p>Our last contender comes from <a href=\"https://www.amazon.com/Rage-Fitness-Blocks-Block-1-Pound/dp/B00L5HZD40/?tag=wbcmb-20\" target=\"_blank\" title=\"https://www.amazon.com/Rage-Fitness-Blocks-Block-1-Pound/dp/B00L5HZD40/?tag=wbcmb-20\">Rage Fitness</a>. Their Premium Powder Chalk is decent quality and will help your grip.</p><p>Let’s start with the pros. This chalk is very affordable and easy to apply. It spreads evenly across your palms and enhances your grip. It will reduce the sweat without drying your skin out and you can use this chalk for a lot of different activities.</p><p>However, this one is pretty messy. You would expect some mess with this type of chalk, but not this much. The powder is extremely fine, almost like baby powder so, although it does feel comfortable on your skin, it creates a lot of dust and doesn’t last long. It falls off pretty quickly (probably because it’s so fine), and it would have been better if it was made of a mixture of fine and gritty powder – it would protect your skin better and it would adhere better.<br/>If you’re using this for long sessions or if your palms sweat a lot, prepare to reapply it frequently.</p><p>The good thing about this chalk is that it’s very gentle to the skin and won’t irritate you. But it’s better suited for mild activities because it just lacks that oomph that would make it withstand something intense.</p><p>With this chalk, you kind of get what you pay for. Yes, it will help your grip and it doesn’t cost much, but it will make a mess and won’t stay on your hands for a long time. In the end, it comes down to your priorities and what you want to use the chalk for.</p>",
